summarize this "1-	Conducting a survey two weeks into the pandemic might not provide sufficient time for researchers to consider the necessary aspects and for individuals to fully adjust to remote work;
2-	In line with the existing literature, including gender in the study is indeed important as it can potentially impact productivity, particularly considering women's responsibilities in caring for infants. However, the study did not highlight these findings due to the timing of data collection. Moreover, marital status which affects work-life balance, should be considered, as being single can lead to fewer responsibilities and more relax time. To ensure a comprehensive understanding of the factors affecting productivity, these factors should be carefully addressed;
3-	 The adjustment to working during unusual hours can have a direct influence on productivity levels and capturing information on time-zone differences will provide valuable insights into the challenges faced by individuals in managing their work and that may impact on productivity. 
4-	the limitation of allowing respondents to choose only three items in Q22 “” should be addressed. The study did not provide a clear rationale for the limitation despite list of more than 10 choices.
"
